61
00:04:49,019 --> 00:04:55,879
And so we had a way to naturally block the transmission of these viruses in human communities

62
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:59,360
by introducing the bacteria to the mosquito population,

63
00:04:59,779 --> 00:05:02,560
essentially almost like vaccinating all the mosquitoes naturally

64
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:06,600
so that they can no longer transmit the viruses between people.

65
00:05:06,759 --> 00:05:10,000
And so it didn't require anything to be done to the human population.

66
00:05:10,019 --> 00:05:11,980
No medicine or drugs for the humans,

67
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:16,660
just focusing on the mosquito and being able to eliminate transmission that way.

68
00:05:17,319 --> 00:05:20,079
And part of the brilliance of what I love about what you've done

69
00:05:20,079 --> 00:05:22,899
is that it doesn't involve insecticides.

70
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,240
It doesn't involve genetic modification.

71
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:29,379
And I'm assuming mosquitoes play a really important role in the ecosystem.

72
00:05:29,379 --> 00:05:31,199
